The DVB reported the explosion injured 11 EPC staff and civilians who were paying electricity bills at the office, but the Eleven Media Group reported that 2 EPC staff and 6 civilians were injured. The RFA also reported that more than 10 people were injured.

assoc_actor_2: Government of Myanmar (2021-) State Administration Council
notes: On 27 September 2021, in Innwa ward in Bago town (Bago district, Bago-East district, Bago region), an unknown group of people threw a grenade at the hundred-household administrator in his house. His leg was injured and was sent to the hospital. Locals believe that the administrator is a military informant.

On 29 May 2021, in Number 16 ward in Hlaingthayar town (Hlaingtharya-East Township, Yangon-North District, Yangon Region), a hand grenade was thrown into the patrolling military vehicle. 5 pedestrians were injured.
On 20 August 2021, in Hlaingtharya (Hlaingtharya-East township, Yangon-North district, Yangon region), the Civil Guerrilla Force-HTY bombed a police station with remote-controlled explosives.

On 3 September 2021, in Mingalar Taung Nyunt town (Mingalartaungnyunt Township, Yangon-East district, Yangon region), two explosions occurred near Fish Sauce Factory. Afterwards, locals also heard the sound of gunfires. Casualties unknown.

On 1 June 2021, in Mingaladon town (Yangon-North District, Yangon Region), an unknown armed group reportedly set off an explosive targeting a Myanmar military truck carrying food supplies. Casualties unknown.
On 7 September 2021, in Pyigyitagon town (Pyigyitagon township, Mandalay district, Mandalay Region), an explosion occurred at a military outpost. Two soldiers were injured.
On 26 April 2021, in Mahaaungmyay township (Mandalay district, Mandalay region), an explosion occurred after a hand grenade was hurled at a high school.

On 4 May 2021, in Bauk Htaw ward, Yankin township (Yangon-East district, Yangon Region), two bombs exploded in front of the hospital recently opened by Senior General Min Aung Hlaing. No injuries reported. Two explosions were reported in the township at around 8pm.

On 19 October 2021, near Ah Shey Pauk Taw village of Yesagyo township (coded as Yesagyo) (Yesagyo township, Pakokku district, Magway region), the joint forces of the MG6 Guerrilla Force and the YSO NO. 1 attacked the telecom tower operated by the Myanmar military owned company Mytel with a bomb. There were no casualties.

actor1: KNU/KNLA: Karen National Union/Karen National Liberation Army
assoc_actor_1: Thaton People's Guerrillas; TPDF: Thaton People's Defense Force
notes: On 11 November 2021, between Naung Bo and Ma Yan Kone villages (Thaton township, Thaton district, Mon state), an unknown group of people bombed a gas pipeline. The KNLA brigade 1, the Thaton PDF and the Thaton People's Guerillas later claimed that they jointly did the bombing. There were no casualties.

On 19 December 2021, in Yinmarbin township (Yinmarbin district, Sagaing region) Myaukyamar People's Defense Force - Yinmarbin and Hero Tigers Force carried out mine attack against the Myanmar military convoy trucks. The attack killed 25 military forces.
